VALUES
  ('019391eb-d362-751f-b1a7-b063ec7df9ca', 'Exploring React Hooks', 'React Hooks are a powerful feature introduced in React 16.8 that allow developers to use state and lifecycle features in functional components. They provide a more concise and readable way of managing state, side effects, and other component behavior compared to traditional class components. In this article, we will dive deep into the various types of hooks like useState, useEffect, useContext, and custom hooks, along with practical examples and best practices.', 'https://via.placeholder.com/150', current_timestamp, current_timestamp),
  ('019391eb-d362-751f-b1a7-b063ec7df9ca', 'Understanding JavaScript Closures', 'JavaScript closures are a fundamental concept that every developer should understand. A closure is created when a function retains access to variables from its outer scope even after the outer function has finished execution. This powerful concept allows for data encapsulation and private variables, making closures indispensable for functional programming. In this article, we’ll explore how closures work, provide code examples, and explain how to leverage them in your code.', 'https://via.placeholder.com/150', current_timestamp, current_timestamp),
  ('019391eb-d362-751f-b1a7-b063ec7df9ca', 'CSS Grid vs Flexbox', 'CSS Grid and Flexbox are two powerful layout techniques in CSS that help developers create responsive and flexible layouts. While both are used to position elements on a webpage, they each have unique advantages. Flexbox excels in one-dimensional layouts, such as aligning items in rows or columns, while CSS Grid provides two-dimensional layouts that give you more control over both rows and columns simultaneously. In this article, we will compare these two layout models in detail and show you when to use each technique.', 'https://via.placeholder.com/150', current_timestamp, current_timestamp),
  ('019391eb-d362-751f-b1a7-b063ec7df9ca', 'Node.js Performance Tuning', 'Node.js is known for its scalability and performance in building high-performance applications. However, as your application grows, performance bottlenecks can arise. In this article, we’ll cover a variety of techniques and best practices to optimize Node.js applications, including asynchronous programming, managing event loops efficiently, and using profiling tools to identify slow functions. Whether you’re building a real-time application or a data-intensive backend, these tips will help ensure your Node.js app runs at peak performance.', 'https://via.placeholder.com/150', current_timestamp, current_timestamp),
  ('019391eb-d362-751f-b1a7-b063ec7df9ca', 'GraphQL vs REST', 'GraphQL and REST are two popular approaches to building APIs. While REST has been around for a long time and is still widely used, GraphQL offers some unique advantages over traditional REST APIs. In this article, we will compare GraphQL and REST, discussing their differences, strengths, and weaknesses. We will also explore scenarios where one might be a better choice than the other and how to decide which one to use for your application based on your specific needs.', 'https://via.placeholder.com/150', current_timestamp, current_timestamp),
  ('019391eb-d362-751f-b1a7-b063ec7df9ca', 'Asynchronous Programming in JavaScript', 'Asynchronous programming in JavaScript is essential for building fast and responsive applications. JavaScript uses callbacks, promises, and async/await to handle asynchronous operations, allowing developers to write non-blocking code. In this article, we will explore these concepts in depth, explaining how they work and providing examples of how to use them effectively. We will also cover common pitfalls in asynchronous programming and provide tips for handling errors and avoiding callback hell.', 'https://via.placeholder.com/150', current_timestamp, current_timestamp),
  ('019391eb-d362-751f-b1a7-b063ec7df9ca', 'Building Scalable Web Applications with Microservices', 'Microservices architecture has become a popular approach for building large-scale web applications. Unlike monolithic applications, where all components are tightly coupled, microservices allow different parts of an application to operate independently. In this article, we’ll discuss the principles of microservices, including service decomposition, communication between services, and the challenges of managing a microservices architecture. We’ll also explore best practices for scaling microservices and ensuring their reliability in production environments.', 'https://via.placeholder.com/150', current_timestamp, current_timestamp),
  ('019391eb-d362-751f-b1a7-b063ec7df9ca', 'Introduction to TypeScript', 'TypeScript is a superset of JavaScript that adds static typing to the language. It’s designed to help developers write more robust and maintainable code by catching errors early during development. In this article, we will introduce TypeScript, cover its key features, and provide examples of how to use it in your projects. Whether you’re working on a small project or a large application, TypeScript can help improve code quality and enhance developer productivity.', 'https://via.placeholder.com/150', current_timestamp, current_timestamp),
  ('019391eb-d362-751f-b1a7-b063ec7df9ca', 'Introduction to Docker for Developers', 'Docker has revolutionized the way we develop, ship, and run applications. By using containers, Docker allows developers to package applications and their dependencies into a portable, consistent environment that can be deployed anywhere. In this article, we’ll provide an introduction to Docker, explain how containers work, and guide you through setting up a simple Docker-based application. We will also explore some of the advanced features of Docker that can help streamline development workflows and improve scalability.', 'https://via.placeholder.com/150', current_timestamp, current_timestamp),
  ('019391eb-d362-751f-b1a7-b063ec7df9ca', 'Mastering Git and GitHub', 'Git and GitHub are essential tools for version control and collaboration in modern software development. Whether you’re working on a solo project or collaborating with a team, understanding Git’s powerful features and GitHub’s collaborative tools can significantly improve your development workflow. In this article, we’ll walk you through the basics of Git, explain key concepts like branches, commits, and merges, and show you how to use GitHub for hosting repositories, managing pull requests, and collaborating with others.', 'https://via.placeholder.com/150', current_timestamp, current_timestamp),
  ('019391eb-d362-751f-b1a7-b063ec7df9ca', 'Implementing Authentication and Authorization in Web Apps', 'Authentication and authorization are crucial parts of any web application that handles user data. Authentication verifies the identity of a user, while authorization determines whether a user has the right to access certain resources. In this article, we will cover the basics of implementing authentication and authorization in web applications, using tools like JWT (JSON Web Tokens) and OAuth. We will also discuss common pitfalls and security practices to ensure your application is secure and user data is protected.', 'https://via.placeholder.com/150', current_timestamp, current_timestamp),
  ('019391eb-d362-751f-b1a7-b063ec7df9ca', 'Building Real-Time Applications with WebSockets', 'WebSockets are a protocol that allows for full-duplex communication between a client and a server, enabling real-time communication in web applications. Whether you’re building a chat application, live updates, or multiplayer games, WebSockets provide a fast, efficient way to send data between clients and servers. In this article, we’ll discuss the basics of WebSockets, show you how to implement them in a Node.js application, and explore the best practices for working with real-time data.', 'https://via.placeholder.com/150', current_timestamp, current_timestamp),
  ('019391eb-d362-751f-b1a7-b063ec7df9ca', 'The Basics of Responsive Web Design', 'Responsive web design is an approach to web development that ensures web pages look good and function properly on devices of all sizes, from desktops to smartphones. By using CSS media queries, flexible layouts, and scalable images, responsive web design allows your website to adapt to different screen sizes and provide a better user experience. In this article, we’ll discuss the fundamentals of responsive design and guide you through creating a responsive layout using HTML and CSS.', 'https://via.placeholder.com/150', current_timestamp, current_timestamp),
  ('019391eb-d362-751f-b1a7-b063ec7df9ca', 'An Introduction to Progressive Web Apps', 'Progressive Web Apps (PWAs) are a new wave of web applications that combine the best features of both web and mobile apps. PWAs offer offline capabilities, push notifications, and a native app-like experience while being accessible through a web browser. In this article, we will explore what PWAs are, how they work, and the tools you need to build your own PWA. We will also discuss how to improve performance and SEO for PWAs to ensure a seamless user experience across devices.', 'https://via.placeholder.com/150', current_timestamp, current_timestamp);